text: On September 11, 2022, an earthquake of the magnitude 7.6 or 7.7 hit Papua New Guinea, in the northern part of Morobe Province. At least seven people died, four others were injured and some people are missing because of landslides. ==References== Category:September 2022 events Category:2022 earthquakes Category:2022 disasters in Oceania Category:21st century in Papua New Guinea Category:Disasters in Papua New Guinea
title: 2022 Papua New Guinea earthquake
